narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned the advanced fundamentals of intro stats. In the particular course, we did a lot of our learning through large problems that required many steps and I benefitted greatly from the set up of our problem sets.
I learned more advanced regression and reviewed AP stats content.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: JDRS!!, clear lectures, great TA's, and the problem sets were extremely interesting and fun to collaborate with others on
Weaknesses: none

A very nice course. It would be nice if he chose one online textbook as the single optional material rather than list several and let us hunt for the information, but that is really a minor complaint. Given we get the two attempts, our quiz content could stand to be a little more difficult to better reflect the exams. There are lots of office hours, wonderful TAs, challenging exams, and interesting lectures. Gradescope is a nice feature.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would totally recommend this course to another student! JDRS is such a great professor and I would take any class that he teaches! The coursework is not extremely difficult to handle because the work is interesting to do! It is very easy to find help and collaborate with others in the class too.

Absolutely! Just because this course wasn't "hard" (only class that hasn't made me cry) doesn't mean you do not learn a lot. It was reasonably challenging and office hours were a good way to make friends. If you have had AP stat take this course, you'll learn about minitab or R and more advanced regression. If you haven't had AP stat take this course, you'll learn important life skills!
